[{"sha":"9dd6b2edb5b6b2f57447087063c72dc53d2e3871","author":{"name":"Jeremy Davis","email":"5d9dc440af010fbc6460682e2df8433253afd211@gmail.com"},"message":"Add virtqueues to the virtio driver.

We now have a `VirtQueue` type (and also private types for its various parts)
that allows initialization and an asynchronous `send_recv` operation. We also
have a `ResponseFuture` type that represents the result of `send_recv`. This
is all untested (can't really test it without a working driver that uses it),
but it was ported from `gfx_prototype.rs`, with only minor changes, so it
_should_ work just fine.

We still have to finish the device initialization in
`virtio/src/lib.rs:init_mmio`, and we need an executor (and an associated
waker type) to poll the `ResponseFuture`s. The executor should probably be in
its own crate.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jeremydavis519/phoenix/commits/9dd6b2edb5b6b2f57447087063c72dc53d2e3871"}]

PiperOrigin-RevId: 382168291
Change-Id: Ia462f38030464fdd71a36f7b23c31066317216e4","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/LongerVision/tensorflow/commits/4214a7e93beea7488250353deab124acdb0e1bba"},{"sha":"f37824765d77abae89f6ab106c3fe7228198b748","author":{"name":"George Karpenkov","email":"bbf3fb1cea1ba929a95f09c9e20513124012c8d3@google.com"},"message":"[XLA:GPU] Do not unroll concat HLO

Concatenation creates many IF- statements, and those tend to perform horribly
on GPU when unrolled, often resulting in excessive register spilling.

Makes BERT step ~16% faster.

On the following synthethic benchmark (simplest possible fusion involving concat):

```
#!/usr/bin/env python3
import sys

def main(n):
  print("""
HloModule module

ENTRY computation {
""")
  for i in range(n):
    print("p%s = f32[1000] parameter(%s)" % (i,i,))
    print("converted%s = f16[1000] convert(p%s)" % (i,i,))
  print("ROOT out = f16[%s] concatenate(" % (n * 1000)),
  for i in range(n):
    print("f16[1000] converted%s" % i),
    if i != n - 1:
      print(", "),
  print("), dimensions={0}")
  print("}")

if __name__ == "__main__":
  main(int(sys.argv[1]))
```

we see ~10% speed-up for n=10, and the speed-up grows to ~50% for n=100.

[{"sha":"9a5fd32800caf4fe77f548e111ed31dbd421cc7c","author":{"name":"Matthias Bläsing","email":"2733b4844ad39354bd21fd2bca55a8804e19a60d@doppel-helix.eu"},"message":"Use j.u.Properties instead of o.o.u.EditableProperties to reduce CPU usage

It was observed, that with a big project, massive time was spend in 
org.openide.util.EditableProperties.addItem(). Given, that none of the
benefits of EditableProperties take hold:

- the properties are used as pure backing store, without the expectation
  of a user to modify them
- the order of the entries is irrelevant
- the file is not put into VCS (it is in the cache path)
- special line break handling is not relevant

the easiest work around is to drop usage of EditableProperties and
use plain Properties.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/apache/netbeans/commits/9a5fd32800caf4fe77f548e111ed31dbd421cc7c"},{"sha":"06ec476b486dd9cf70f2b3034ee092a434a92a50","author":{"name":"Matthias Bläsing","email":"2733b4844ad39354bd21fd2bca55a8804e19a60d@doppel-helix.eu"},"message":"Merge pull request #3061 from matthiasblaesing/excessive_cpu_usage_lsp_client
